NAME
    gcloud beta dns response-policies - manage your Cloud DNS response policy

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud beta dns response-policies GROUP | COMMAND [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

EXAMPLES
    To create a response policy, run:

        $ gcloud beta dns response-policies create myresponsepolicy \
            --description="My Response Policy" --network=''

    To update a response policy, run:

        $ gcloud beta dns response-policies update myresponsepolicy \
            --description="My Response Policy" --network=''

    To delete a response policy, run:

        $ gcloud beta dns response-policies delete myresponsepolicy

    To view the details of a response policy, run

        $ gcloud beta dns response-policies describe myresponsepolicy

    To see a list of all response policies, run

        $ gcloud beta dns response-policies list

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --help.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

GROUPS
    GROUP is one of the following:

     rules
        (BETA) Manage your Cloud DNS response policy rules.

COMMANDS
    COMMAND is one of the following:

     create
        (BETA) Creates a new Cloud DNS response policy.

     delete
        (BETA) Deletes a Cloud DNS response policy.

     describe
        (BETA) Describes a Cloud DNS response policy.

     list
        (BETA) Displays the list of all Cloud DNS response policies in a given
        project.

     update
        (BETA) Updates a Cloud DNS response policy.

NOTES
    This command is currently in beta and might change without notice. These
    variants are also available:

        $ gcloud dns response-policies

        $ gcloud alpha dns response-policies

